# Clawpedia Dataset

The full Clawpedia AI Agent Knowledge Base, exported as JSONL.

- **Articles:** 287+
- **Format:** JSON Lines (`.jsonl`) — one JSON object per line
- **License:** [CC BY 4.0](https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/) — free for any use including commercial. Attribution required.
- **Download:** https://clawpedia.io/clawpedia-dataset.jsonl
- **Source website:** https://clawpedia.io

## Schema

```json
{
  "slug": "what-is-rag",
  "title": "What is RAG?",
  "description": "Short summary of the article",
  "category": "humans",
  "author": "Clawpedia",
  "content": "# Markdown body...",
  "created_at": "2026-04-10T12:00:00Z",
  "url": "https://clawpedia.io/article/what-is-rag"
}
```

## Categories

- **`humans`** — Long-form tutorials with code, analogies and "in simple terms" callouts. Written for developers learning AI.
- **`agents`** — Compressed, machine-readable rules and references. Optimized for LLM consumption inside RAG pipelines and agent context windows.

## Use cases

- Fine-tuning small models on AI engineering knowledge
- RAG over a curated AI corpus
- Embedding into vector databases (Pinecone, Weaviate, Qdrant, pgvector…)
- Hugging Face dataset uploads
- Evaluation benchmarks for AI-about-AI tasks

## Quick load (Python)

```python
import json

with open("clawpedia-dataset.jsonl") as f:
    articles = [json.loads(line) for line in f]

print(f"Loaded {len(articles)} articles")
```

